{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/vop/DASH--vertex_edge_formats-1.0/DASH-vertex_edge_formats-icon.svg", "type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "vertex_edge_formats", "version": "1.0", "namespace": "DASH"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Vertex/Edge Formats"], "extent": [50, 72]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Convert vertex or edge ids between single id and pair of ids formats."], "extent": [72, 150]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [150, 165], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Utility to control the format conversion between single id and pair of ids, for vertices and edges, with support for arrays and splitting."], "extent": [165, 306]}, {"type": "table", "thead": [{"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": ["Element Type "], "role": "th", "extent": [306, 322], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": ["Single ID "], "role": "th", "extent": [322, 339], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 8, "text": ["Pair of IDs"], "role": "th", "extent": [339, 361]}], "divider": false}], "body": [{"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": ["Vertex "], "role": "td", "extent": [361, 371], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": ["Linear Vertex "], "role": "td", "extent": [371, 391], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Primitive ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["&"]}, " Local Vertex"], "extent": [391, 427]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": ["Edge "], "role": "td", "extent": [427, 435], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": null, "value": "/vex/halfedges", "type": "link", "text": ["Half-Edge"], "fullpath": "/vex/halfedges.html"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [435, 468], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Point A ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["&"]}, " Point B"], "extent": [468, 497]}]}], "divider": false}]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [497, 509], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Geometry"], "extent": [509, 520], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Geometry used in the operation, with the default being the Attribute VOP SOP\u2019s  first input, i.e. ", {"type": "code", "text": ["opinput:0"]}, ". But the drop-down menu provides presets like a file on disk, an operator path or a spare input."], "extent": [538, 750]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "geometry"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Class"], "extent": [750, 757], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The conversion is either of Vertex or Edge elements."], "extent": [772, 830]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "class"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Element 1"], "extent": [830, 841], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If used solo, it ought to be a linear vertex id or the half-edge id."], "extent": [862, 936]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "element1_s1"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Element 2"], "extent": [936, 947], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This index will be used in conjunction with ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Element 1"]}, " for vertex or edge sourcing if either; the parameter value is greater than ", {"type": "code", "text": ["-1"]}, " or, if there is a connection on the homonymous port."], "extent": [968, 1164]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If so, vertices are sourced by a pair of prim id and local vertex id and edges are sourced by a pair of point ids. The latter will follow the rules in ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Assess Input Edges"]}, " to determine which hedge is targeted by the pair."], "extent": [1164, 1393]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "element2_s1"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Vertices/Edges Format"], "extent": [1393, 1416], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Determine if the conversion is from a single format to pair format or vice-versa."], "extent": [1432, 1519]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "format"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Split into Pair of Arrays"], "extent": [1519, 1546], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When and only the format conversion deals with arrays and from ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Single to Pair"]}, ", activating this will have the pairs split into two arrays instead of alternating in a single array."], "extent": [1567, 1752]}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 4, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--vertex_edge_formats-1.0/DASH-vertex_edge_formats-help_split_256.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [1752, 1828]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "split_pairs"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Assess Input Edges"], "extent": [1828, 1848], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Input edges can be sourced from a single hedge id (", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Element 1"]}, ") or a pair of point ids (", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Element 2"]}, " and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Element 2"]}, "). For the latter this parameter determines if either the order of the points targets strictly an hedge with matching source and destination points or if, failing that it falls back to any valid hedge with such pair (default behavior). "], "extent": [1870, 2233]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For both input methods, ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Force Primary Hedge"]}, " will guarantee that whatever valid hedge is considered input or output, that the equivalent primary hedge is considered instead."], "extent": [2233, 2415]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "assess_edges"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "extent": [2415, 2423], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Description"], "extent": [2423, 2436], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["String to replace any automatic description on top of the node in the network view. The pilcrow \u00b6 button enables multi-line text."], "extent": [2457, 2592]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "description"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "load_example_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "load_example", "indent": 0, "text": [" Vertex Edge Formats"], "role": "item", "extent": [2592, 2627], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This HDA example scene."], "extent": [2685, 2717]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"examplefile": "/demos/vop/vertex_edge_formats_demo.hda"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "text": "Parameters"}], "title": ["Vertex/Edge Formats"], "summary": ["Convert vertex or edge ids between single id and pair of ids formats."]}